  "prompt": "What is Instagram's hourly comment limit?",
  "response": "As of the information available up to October 2023, Instagram has various limits in place to prevent spam and misuse. For comments, the specific hourly limit can vary based on several factors, including the age and activity level of your account. Generally, newer accounts or those that have been flagged for potential spam may face stricter limitations.\n\nA commonly cited figure for comment limits is around 60 comments per hour. However, this number can fluctuate, and consistently exceeding these limits can lead to temporary restrictions or account suspension.\n\nTo avoid hitting these limits, it's best to focus on genuine interactions and refrain from spamming comments, especially repetitively or in a short period. Always check Instagram's latest community guidelines and updates, as policies and limits can change over time.",
